text.tspan: #Place the red LED between J12 & any point
on the blue (-’ve) rail.
The long anode pin is +’ve while the shorter pin
is the -’ve cathode and is on the side of the
slightly flattened part of the clear LED plastic.
You need to get this right or it won’t light up!
Notice inside the LED the cathode (-’ve) the
metal end is larger than the anodes pole
